{"overview":"This C-minor sonata-form movement unfolds across 312 bars with a brooding Grave introduction that punctuates both the development and coda, framing a turbulent Allegro driven by stormy unison tremolo textures and lyrical arabesques. Its most distinctive feature is the cyclical return of the slow Grave material at structurally pivotal moments, combined with a bold chromatic-mediant shift to E major at the heart of the development and a striking modal mixture inflection that briefly brightens the recapitulation's second theme into C major before the minor-mode close.","cross_piece_tags":["sonata_form","chromatic_mediant","modal_mixture","dramatic","tragic","arpeggiated_bass","lyrical","circle_of_fifths"]}
